        <p><a href="" class="open-asset-modal" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#ModalFigf04"><span class="sci-ico-fileFigure"></span>Figure 04</a> shows the countries of origin of the authors of the analyzed scientific publications, as well as the type of publication involved ¾ SCP (Single Country Publications) and MCP (Multiple Country Publications). The United States leads in single-country publications, with over 2,000 such publications. In contrast, China stands out in international collaboration, surpassing the United States in multiple-country publications. However, China has fewer single-country publications, with just under 2,000 during the period analyzed.</p>
        <p>
          <div class="row fig" id="f04">
